    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><br><br><h5> This article is reformatted from originally published at <a href="https://www.cantorsparadise.com/this-mathematics-paper-is-just-2-words-long-611781c687f5"><strong>TDS(Towards Data Science)</strong></a></h5></br><h5> <a href="https://piggsboson.medium.com/?source=post_page-----611781c687f5--------------------------------">Author : Sunny Labh</a> </h5></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content4 cid-tt5SM2WLsM" id="content4-2" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row justify-content-center">
                    <div class="title col-md-12 col-lg-9">
                        <h3 class="mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-2">
                            <strong>This Mathematics Paper Is Just 2 Words Long</h3></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5 text-muted">The shortest research paper ever published</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><span>M</span>athematics is a wonderful language. Unlike, literature, it can convey its significance with just the help of diagrams and geometric figures. The culture of scientific and mathematical publications has been going on for ages now. It’s hard to believe that <em>arXiv</em> is now nearly 31 years old and receives <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ArXiv" target="_self">over 16000 articles and paper</a><em>s</em> every month from all across the world. Thousands of research papers are published every month on several disciplines of the sciences, economics, sociology, literature, and mathematics, and more than half of them are not even read by people and go unnoticed. Only a few percentages come into the limelight with some <em>exceptions</em> and those are the ones that leave an impact.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">I have been an avid reader of scientific and mathematics journals, primarily the ones that come under my research domain and sometimes I come across some brilliantly exceptional ones. For instance, in some research papers, the titles are longer than the <em>abstract</em>. This research paper, for example, has one of the longest titles (though not longer than the <em>abstract</em>) in the history of scientific publication.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
